The paper discusses the use of LSTM networks for benchmarking on image and text datasets, which suggests that it could fall under several sub-categories. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as it deals with the use of neural networks for various applications. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper uses the MNIST dataset, which is a popular dataset for image classification tasks. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper explores the effect of different architectural and hyperparameter choices on performance. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also possible as the paper uses the UW3 dataset, which is a handwritten text recognition dataset. Finally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a broad category that could also encompass this paper's content.
